                <head>178. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The results of the June 1, 1966, presidential elections in the Dominican Republic
                    were reported to President <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> in a
                    June 3 memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Rostow</persName> who wrote
                    that an “impressive” number of voters, approximately 1.4 million from an
                    estimated 1.7 million, went to the polls. <persName corresp="#p_RWW1"
                        >Rostow</persName> summarized that <persName corresp="#p_BJ1"
                        >Balaguer</persName> had captured 57.09 percent of the vote; <persName
                        corresp="#p_BJ4">Bosch</persName> 39.17 percent and Bonnelly 3.4 percent.
                        (<persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> Library, National Security
                    File, Country File, Dominican Republic, Vol. XVI)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
